summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 37015, entitled an "An Ordinance providing for the laying off, opening, widening, extending and establishing of Henderson Street from Rainier Avenue eastward, to the line of navigability in Lake Washington; providing for the condemnation, appropriation, taking and damaging of land and other property necessary therefor, and providing that the entire cost of said improvement shall be paid by special assessments upon the property especially benefited in the manner provided by law approved January 31, 1917, and published February 6, 1917.
